{
  "stem": "12462.3",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I knew this wouldn't last long, because there would have to be a successor to Jackson, who had high rank, and eventually the Subsequent Proceedings would become the main trial.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And that's, of course, what happened.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Colonel Taylor, Colonel Tulford Taylor, became the designate-- the designated successor to Justice Jackson, and he took over the Subsequent Proceedings.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I then became head of the Economics Division and later head of the IG Farben trial team and later head of the Publications Division under General Taylor.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "General Taylor was promoted-- Colonel Taylor was promoted to general some time in the spring of 1945.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was very plain from the time we began that people who were, you know, high authority in Nazi Germany reached far beyond the 24 people that we indicted in the first trial.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And Justice Jackson, in his early reports to President Truman, indicated that there would have to be some subsequent trials, but that he was only committed to the first trial.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And very early, he indicated and, in fact, this-- in December of 1945, that he was probably planning on having Colonel Taylor become his successor, or recommending that he be made his successor.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And indeed, this was carried on to where Tulford Taylor was made the deputy chief counsel for Subsequent Proceedings, as well as for the main trial.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And as soon as Justice Jackson resigned in October, just after the first trial was done, General McNarney, the head of the US military forces in Germany, appointed then Colonel Taylor to be US Chief of Counsel for War Crimes.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The International Military Tribunal.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "In the Subsequent Proceedings, the tribunals were merely referred to as the American Military Tribunal for Case 1 or Case 2 or whatever it was, and we had 12 cases.",
      "word_count": 30
    }
  ],
